"step_by_step_thinking": "The term anxiolysis refers to a state of reduced anxiety. It is often used as a precursor to sedation, hence the continuum to sedation. Conscious sedation is a form of sedation that allows patients to still respond to verbal commands and maintain their airway. Deep sedation is typically defined as a level of sedation where patients are unable to respond to verbal commands or maintain their airway without assistance. Minimal sedation refers to a light level of sedation, often used for minor procedures. General anaesthesia is a state of unconsciousness where patients are unable to respond to any stimuli. Based on the continuum to sedation, anxiolysis would fall under conscious sedation.",
